$ Excel functions: seperating arguments with semicolon or commas

If arguments in an → Microsoft/Office/Excel/functions[Excel worksheet functions] are to be separated by semicolons or commas is determined by Windows setting
→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/intl_cpl#intl-cpl-date-time-formats[List separator].

When using → development/languages/VBA[Visual Basic for Applications] to assign formulas, the separator is always a comma.
